    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any number of various card games for two, three, or four players, each typically being dealt seven, nine, or ten cards, in which the object is to match cards into sets and sequences.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>適用於兩位、三位或四位玩家等任意數量的各種紙牌遊戲。每位玩家通常被發送七張、九張或十張牌卡，遊戲目的是將卡片配對成組和序列。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eine beliebige Anzahl verschiedener Kartenspiele für zwei, drei oder vier Spieler, bei denen jeder üblicherweise sieben, neun oder zehn Karten erhält und bei denen es darum geht, Karten zu Sets und Folgen zusammenzufügen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
